Looks like you want the [Graph API][1] to [list the groups][2] and pull out the one you want. The [GraphGroup][3] object has the **descriptor** property.

The [Samples Repo for the .net client libraries][4] has some code to show how the api works.

```lang-cs
        /// &lt;summary&gt;
        /// Returns all groups in account.
        /// &lt;/summary&gt;
        /// &lt;returns&gt;&lt;/returns&gt;
        [ClientSampleMethod]
        public PagedGraphGroups GetAllGroups()
        {
            VssConnection connection = Context.Connection;
            GraphHttpClient graphClient = connection.GetClient&lt;GraphHttpClient&gt;();
            PagedGraphGroups groups = graphClient.ListGroupsAsync().Result;

            foreach (var group in groups.GraphGroups)
            {
                LogGroup(group);
            }

            return groups;
        }
```



